subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Female (
Fig. 63
). Head 1.4× wider than high (from the vertex to the base of the clypeus) in frontal view (
Fig. 65
); anterior margin of clypeus (
Fig. 65
) straight; genal bridge absent; OOD: POD = 1.1; A12: A11 = 1.25–1.5; pronotum dark brown to black, and width of posterior margin 1.8× length of anterior to posterior margin; dorsum of propodeum laterally and upper portion of side with dense striae, and medially largely smooth; each of T1–T5 (
Fig. 68
) subapically with a row of punctures and medially absent forming incomplete groove; T2–T4 (
Fig. 68
) laterally with light spots, the distance between two lateral spots more than the length of the spot.

Male (
Fig. 64
). Clypeus wholly with sparse punctures; vertex with dense to moderate punctures, POD 1.1× OOD; pronotal anterior carina present and medially minutely absent, dorsum of pronotum (
Fig. 67
) sparsely punctate; lateral side of pronotum (
Fig. 66
) ventrally striate; ventral surface of mid femur smooth, without punctures nor setae; each of T1–T6 except base yellow; T3–T5 (
Fig. 69
) basally with sparse punctures, apically impunctate and smooth; T7 (
Fig. 70
) only basally with a few sparse and shallow punctures, apex with deep notch, and tipped lobes narrowly rounded.
